Title:

“Conservation Laws of Meaning: Mathematics, Chemistry, and the Geometry of Stable Discourse.”

Core claim:

All stable languages conserve something under transformation.
Instability arises when transformations violate conserved quantities.

Mathematics conserves invariance.
Chemistry conserves energy.
Ethical discourse must conserve proportionality.
Institutional legitimacy conserves procedural symmetry.

This is not mystical.
It’s cross-domain structural isomorphism.

